        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 18 at 12:07AM CDT by NWS North Platte NE</headline>
        <description>At 1207 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Newport, or 10 miles east of Bassett, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Atkinson, Stuart, Newport, and Emmet.

This includes Highway 20 between mile markers 267 and 300.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 400 AM CDT for
north central Nebraska.</instruction>
